The paper deals with measuring clustering in directed graphs, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper focuses on analyzing real-world networks and their properties. The second likely category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper proposes a new family of directed closure coefficients that can be used in machine learning tasks. The third likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper examines the theoretical behavior of the closure coefficients under a directed configuration model. The fourth likely category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), as the paper studies the frequency of triadic closure in directed graphs from the perspective of the node initiating closure. The fifth likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper uses the closure coefficients as predictors in machine learning tasks.
